Vice President Mike Pence visited a Customs and Border Protection facility in McAllen, Texas, and praised the professionalism and compassion of the agents. He criticized Democrats for referring to the facilities as "concentration camps" and emphasized the need to address the crisis at the southern border. Pence expressed gratitude to Senator Lindsey Graham and other lawmakers for their efforts to support border security and close loopholes in immigration laws. He highlighted the overcrowding at the facilities and called for immediate action to address the situation. Pence pledged to provide the necessary resources and support to secure the border and provide humanitarian assistance to those who enter the country illegally. The Vice President urged Congress to take action and bring an end to the crisis.